kohuhu
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Pittosporum tenifoluim</i>, a small tree or shrub, related to tarata, often used for ornamental hedges; (black) matipo
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also kohukohu, karo
Pronunciation:
Notes: [1846 Raoul Choix de plantes de la Nouvelle-Z'elande Cohou-cohu [P. obcordatum] (And)]
Citations
